  <bioghist id="aspace_1152abee56f47077344d7e99073c0b1c">
    <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
<p>Vera Rony was the executive director of the Workers Defense League (WDL), a workers' rights organization founded in 1936 which throughout its history has focused its advocacy on defending the legal rights of sharecroppers' and farm workers' organizations, helping soldiers fight dishonorable discharges, and organizing a training program to prepare minority youth to enter the building trades. Rony also served as the Founding Director and first Affirmative Action Officer of the Labor Management Studies Program at Stony Brook University and was involved with the civil rights group Congress of Racial Equality (CORE). She was the Executive Producer of <emph render="italic">The Uprising of '34</emph>, a 1995 PBS documentary which explores the 1934 General Textile Strike in which 500,000 Southern mill laborers walked off their jobs.</p>  </bioghist>
