  <scopecontent id="aspace_bdc53bad799cb3ba717ba62d2b31d3d7">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>This collection contains news clippings, publiciations, printed ephemera, corrrespondence, and research files related to Rony's work at Stony Brook, the WDL, CORE, and other groups; Rony's published and unpublished writings; research and administrative files for <emph render="italic">The Uprising of '34</emph>, VHS tapes and audiocassettes, mostly related to <emph render="italic">The Uprising of '34</emph>; and personal correspondence and photographs. </p><p>This collection is a rich source of information for researchers interested in the history of the civil rights and labor movements in the United States, particularly in the South, in the 1950s, 1960s, and 1970s. The collection is especially relevant to researchers interested in the activities of the WDL, CORE or other organizations Rony was involved with during her decades of activism, as well as reseachers specfically interested in works in the agricultural or textile industries. </p>  </scopecontent>
